cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MA 

This paper deals with the problem of allocating resources or tasks among agents, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of monetary transfers to achieve envy-freeness and equitability involves optimization and algorithmic techniques, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the concept of superadditivity is related to mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
